Jacobi jumped up onto his horse and prepared for the journey back to Mayazar. It had been a long ride here and a longer stay, or at least to him, it felt like it. He turned his steed towards the exit of town and kicked.

//Time to get my reward//

[[Chapter 2:The Mountain Pass]]

Jacobi waited for a few minutes before siezing an opportunity to attack. The cultist turned to survey a different area of the mountain range, and as he did so, Jacobi struck. Sprinting from his rock at full speed, the cultist had little time to react before Jacobi plunged his $weapon through the madman's neck. Re and black blood oozed from the wound, like pus from a sore. The smell was wretched and unlike anything Jacobi had smelled before, and he had killed many things in his time.

//Whatever they've done to themselves, it can't be healthy,//he thought, wiping the blood from his blade. As he did so, a thought came to him.
//If I take this man's robe and use their hidden entrance, I may be able to get through their defenses more easily.//
And with that Jacobi removed the robe from the cultist. Beneath these however, was a sight Jacobi wished he had not seen. The man's body was covered in scars with scriptures burnt across his flesh. Small tentacle like tendrils protruded along his arms and legs, as though a foul beast was being born within his sickly flesh.
//Time to leave, I'll return here at sundown,// Jacobi thought, dragging the corpse into hiding within a set of bushes.
(Cultist Robe found!)
(Hidden entrance found!)
[[Return to Outpost|Outpost]]
<<set $robe to true>>
<<set $cultTrack to true>>

Unrolling the letter, Jacobi's heat sank into his stomach as he began to read.

//Ser Jacobi Kozlov,//

//If you are alive to read this then I assume you have rid the northern Keep of cultist scum. As per our arragement you are to recieve 500 gold pieces for your service to the realm upon your return. But now I must demand you complete one final task for me, should you wish a peaceful future. The King's Guard, Ser Joren Fletcher, I have sent with this letter is to escort you to the Eastern fishing village Fjorna, just a day's ride from Salazhar Keep.//

//Reports sent by carrier pidgeon from our Northern Allies suggest that although many of the cultists escaped to the Keep, men were seen leaving their forces and taking ships to sail around the mountains. As Fjorna is the first village past this mountain range, military experts believe that the town could now very well be infested with these scum.//

//We are to take no chances with these people, and by order of the myself, King Edward Twinning, I demand you go to this village and root out any possible cultist infestation. Burn it to the ground and leave no soul alive, for the infection of the cultist's madness spreads fast and we cannot risk an uprising from within our lands.//

//Burn the village to the ground, and destroy the infestation. Should you refuse this order, you will be branded an an enemy of the realm. You, and the ones you love, will be drawn and quartered in the streets. Complete this task, and you will be free to live out your final days in peace.//

//His Greatness,//
//King Edward Twinnig III//


[[Chapter 3:True Colours]]

//One final hut before leaving through the Smithy. The smoke should almost be thick enough for my escape,// thought Jacobi, lighting a final torch and throwing it at the hut's front door. The fire took shortly after, blocking in any who might still have been inside.

//And all this time, all these deaths and not a single cultist. Twinning you idiot,// he thought heading briskly towards the Smithy.
(-1 Torch)

[[Continue Onwards|Fjorna Village]]
<<set $houseBurnt to $houseBurnt+1>>
<<set $torches to $torches-1>>

After speaking with the commander to organize his sleeping arrangements, Jacobi walked out towards the Keep, now silent after the battle, to brood over his current affairs. The night breeze fell through the valley from over the mountain peaks, and was all that could be heard as the remaining men in the outpost slept.

//I can do what he wants and leave, but knowing that bastard of a King I don't think ther will ever be an end to this,// the wind whipping around his hair and leather straps. The empty night was the only peace he had found in a long while.

He stared out towards the edge of camp at Ser Joren's tent, just outside of the Outpost's barrier.//If he doesn't want people to realize a King's Guard was sent here then why didn't Twinning just send a messenger?// he thought, a realization striking him immediately after.

//He's going to kill me when I finish Twinning's dirty work,// the thought ringing out in his mind like a church bell, all too obvious.
//Either I take my chances and do what the King wants for Cassandra, or I can escape home and get her the hell out before it's too late.//
[[Sleep For The Night|Sleep]]
[[Escape in the Night|Escape]]
<<set $deadJ to false>>

Jacobi and Ser Joren arrived at their destination in the mid-afternoon, a rocky outcrop on a hill overlooking the small fishing village of Fjorna and the sea on which it sat. From here the whole village could be seen, what little of it there was. 

Barely a dozen houses were scattered about the shoreline, two of which were clearly boathouses and another the town's smithy. All the others merely seemed to be housing for the townsfolk, small crops and farm animals penned hapazardly around the houses. 

"Take a good look down there," said Ser Joren, dismountin his horse and thudding to the ground. His horse breathed a sigh of relief at the loss of weight from Joren's thick armour.
"You'll need to know your way around for tonight."

//That's right,// thought Jacobi. //This town won't exist after tonight of Twinnig gets what he wants.// They began setting up camp, and a thought continued to twitch in Jacobi's mind.
//Will he really kill me when I'm done here. I could risk getting him first, but then it will look suspicious if I return without him.// He began to prepare the campfire, sparking at twigs with his tinderbox.

//If I go in there, I could perhaps escape in the chaos without being seen. But a good deal of people will die.// His mind turned to Cassandra.
//They can all die so long as she lives.// He stood up and look over the town once more, scanning for an escape route.
//There, the horses hitched behind the Smithy. If I leave through there I can escape home and get Cassandra back.//
//Or kill ser Joren and end this madness now.//
[[Burn The Village]]
[[Attack Ser Joren]]

Jacobi tore open the note. Of course no one but the King would use her as blackmail. And without her medication she would most likely die within a week, but of course he knew that. She had contracted a sickness years ago when a roaming orc band attacked nearby lands, spreading their disease and filth as they went.

It had hit her strong, and Jacobi had worked hard to get enough supplies to ensure it did not engulf her. The final job in Toreal from William was supposed to be his final expedition, as the gold he had been promised would have more than enough to get her proper medical attention from a sactioned Alchemist.

Opening the note, he read:

//If you are reading this, then you have failed to follow my orders, and the town of Fjorna still stands. Infested with cult scum in every nook and cranny. Return to Mayazar without completing this task or you will find your wife's head impaled at the city gates.//

//You have little medical supplies left, Monster Hunter. Do this, and you may yet live.//

//King Edward Twinning III//

Jacobi, crumpled the note in his hands.
//Twinning dies tonight.//
[[Prepare to Assault Mayazar|Preparation]]

The ride to Mayzar took barely half a day, as Jacobi's parents had been sure to build the home he now owned quite close to civilization. Stopping at a rocky outcrop just outside of the city, Jacobi felt it wise to wait for nightfall before entering the city.

//I'm already recognizable, but with this uniform, the rain jacket and the darkness, I shouldn't be bothered by anyone until I reach the palace gates, and even then I doubt they'll stop me if I show them my service pin.//He grinned, never did Jacobi think his work as a city Guard would help him in his life afterwards. He had only held onto the clothes at Cassandra's request, saying how she was so proud of his distinguished work within their ranks.

His mind returned to the task at hand after the thought of Cassandra crossed his mind.
//Time to get moving,// he thought, as the sun began to drop below the horizon.

[[Enter Mayazar]]

The ride back to Mayazar had been long and cold, and Jacobi had dreams of resting peacefully in his soft bed at home on the plains. 
//Of course, when this is all over, I'll get some much needed sleep,// he thought, his horse steadily trodding towards the imposing city gates of Mayazar.
Jacobi waved ahead, signalling the on-duty guards to allow him to enter, and quickly flashed the King's orders for them to see so he could continues without their harrassment.
//I should go collect my reward from William,// he contemplated, riding towards the centre of town.

[[Go see William|GuardHouse]]
